23
00:02:24,859 --> 00:02:28,438
I don't mind, but why can't we all eat together?

24
00:02:29,199 --> 00:02:30,999
You don't mind?

25
00:02:30,999 --> 00:02:33,099
Why would I?

26
00:02:35,998 --> 00:02:37,798
I'll bring them over.

27
00:02:49,759 --> 00:02:51,819
Here, Professor, Madam.

28
00:02:53,358 --> 00:02:54,858
Hello.

29
00:02:54,858 --> 00:02:57,278
This is my high school classmate, Qiao Jingjing.

30
00:02:57,278 --> 00:03:01,578
Jingjing, this is my mentor, Professor Zhang, and his wife, Professor Wang.

31
00:03:01,578 --> 00:03:03,479
Hi, Professor Zhang. Hi, Professor Wang.

32
00:03:03,479 --> 00:03:06,579
Hello. Hello.

33
00:03:08,558 --> 00:03:10,939
Come, have a seat.

34
00:03:13,879 --> 00:03:18,599
Here. You can put this here. Have a seat.

35
00:03:18,599 --> 00:03:20,158
Okay.

36
00:03:20,158 --> 00:03:25,958
Xiao Yu, when did you have such a beautiful high school classmate?

37
00:03:27,479 --> 00:03:31,538
I feel like I've seen you somewhere.

38
00:03:33,278 --> 00:03:35,278
Is today your birthday, Professor Wang?

39
00:03:35,278 --> 00:03:36,778
No.

40
00:03:36,778 --> 00:03:42,459
Today is actually our wedding anniversary.

41
00:03:42,459 --> 00:03:45,659
We will have dinner here every year to celebrate it.

42
00:03:45,659 --> 00:03:48,559
We actually booked a table,

43
00:03:48,559 --> 00:03:53,879
but for some reason, they couldn't find the record.

44
00:03:53,879 --> 00:03:56,099
They must have a lot of customers.

45
00:03:56,099 --> 00:04:01,619
Professor, if today is your wedding anniversary, then we...

46
00:04:02,839 --> 00:04:04,358
It's no bother!

47
00:04:04,358 --> 00:04:06,318
You know very well that

48
00:04:06,318 --> 00:04:09,678
both of us like company.

49
00:04:09,678 --> 00:04:15,079
Having a meal with you two, one of which is a pretty girl,

50
00:04:15,079 --> 00:04:19,118
it can't possibly be better than this, can it?

51
00:04:19,118 --> 00:04:21,999
Okay. I'll order food then.

52
00:04:21,999 --> 00:04:23,539
No need.

53
00:04:23,539 --> 00:04:26,158
We are its patrons for several decades.

54
00:04:26,158 --> 00:04:29,999
I know very well which dish is the best.

55
00:04:29,999 --> 00:04:33,639
You two just enjoy a free meal today.

56
00:04:33,639 --> 00:04:36,679
You took their room first.

57
00:04:36,679 --> 00:04:38,618
Excuse me.

58
00:04:41,079 --> 00:04:42,838
Hello. Ready to order?

59
00:04:42,838 --> 00:04:44,138
Yes.

60
00:04:45,238 --> 00:04:48,138
For the cold dish, one portion of smoked fish,

61
00:04:48,138 --> 00:04:51,099
drunken chicken, candied lotus root,

62
00:04:51,099 --> 00:04:54,079
and the Four-Treasures-In-Huadiao-Wine. That's all.

63
00:04:54,079 --> 00:04:56,238
As for the hot dish,

64
00:04:56,238 --> 00:04:59,030
red braised pork belly is a must-have.

65
00:04:59,030 --> 00:05:01,270
Then one portion of stir-fried prawn.

66
00:05:01,998 --> 00:05:05,798
- And then... 
 - Professor, wouldn't it be too oily? We should have something light.

67
00:05:05,798 --> 00:05:07,318
This is a rare occasion.

68
00:05:07,318 --> 00:05:10,239
Also, you youngsters are here today.

69
00:05:10,239 --> 00:05:14,259
Sautéed peas. Fish noodle. Those will do.

70
00:05:14,259 --> 00:05:15,638
Okay.

71
00:05:17,759 --> 00:05:20,118
Are you staying in Shanghai? No travel plans?

72
00:05:20,118 --> 00:05:23,318
No, I have some business here.

73
00:05:23,318 --> 00:05:25,438
I was looking for you to discuss something.

74
00:05:25,438 --> 00:05:31,579
Yu Tu, I have dealt with your problem.

75
00:05:32,639 --> 00:05:35,739
I know that Guan Zai and you

76
00:05:35,739 --> 00:05:40,079
have reached a bottleneck in the model research project.

77
00:05:40,079 --> 00:05:44,158
The institute has always played safe.

78
00:05:44,158 --> 00:05:49,139
You have to understand that that's how we survived thus far.

79
00:05:49,139 --> 00:05:52,158
Guaranteeing success is the most important part.

80
00:05:52,158 --> 00:05:54,638
Redundancy is always good

81
00:05:54,638 --> 00:05:57,879
because we can't afford to fail.

82
00:05:58,519 --> 00:06:01,910
However, the times have changed.

83
00:06:01,910 --> 00:06:03,830
Our nation has become stronger,

84
00:06:03,839 --> 00:06:06,858
so we also need to change our mindset.

85
00:06:06,858 --> 00:06:09,899
We ought to encourage the young to innovate.

86
00:06:09,899 --> 00:06:14,038
I can understand why you suddenly said you wanted to quit.

87
00:06:14,038 --> 00:06:16,899
That's why I gave you a break.

88
00:06:16,899 --> 00:06:19,179
Let you take your mind off.

89
00:06:19,738 --> 00:06:23,599
During this whole month, I was busy as well.

90
00:06:23,599 --> 00:06:28,098
I discussed with Director Hu many times.

91
00:06:30,718 --> 00:06:35,618
The institute's attitude has now softened.

92
00:06:37,879 --> 00:06:41,058
Your project represents the future.

93
00:06:41,058 --> 00:06:46,818
The higher-ups have their eye on Guan Zai and you,

94
00:06:46,818 --> 00:06:48,918
the future leaders.

95
00:06:48,918 --> 00:06:53,619
We don't want you to follow the old mindset and refuse to change.

96
00:06:54,499 --> 00:06:57,139
Your break is almost over.

97
00:06:57,139 --> 00:07:03,799
When you return, revise the proposal with Guan Zai again

98
00:07:03,799 --> 00:07:07,778
and try to get the institute's support.

99
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:19,779
Did you hear me?

100
00:07:27,398 --> 00:07:30,399
Do you still want to quit?

101
00:07:31,079 --> 00:07:33,359
Let's not talk about business.

102
00:07:33,359 --> 00:07:35,398
Relax.

103
00:07:35,398 --> 00:07:36,438
Come.

104
00:07:36,438 --> 00:07:38,138
Let him speak.

105
00:07:39,998 --> 00:07:42,038
Do you have other reasons?

106
00:07:47,138 --> 00:07:48,738
Professor,

107
00:07:51,599 --> 00:07:53,399
I left

108
00:07:56,199 --> 00:07:58,099
for money.

109
00:08:16,998 --> 00:08:18,998
I understand.

110
00:08:20,539 --> 00:08:22,639
Many people

111
00:08:23,759 --> 00:08:26,219
have left over the years.

112
00:08:26,219 --> 00:08:30,599
I can understand their choices.

113
00:08:32,998 --> 00:08:35,958
I'm just a bit disappointed.

114
00:08:38,838 --> 00:08:40,919
Yu Tu,

115
00:08:43,238 --> 00:08:45,899
you've really disappointed me.

116
00:08:45,899 --> 00:08:47,840
You're my proudest student.

117
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:49,510
I thought...

118
00:08:55,079 --> 00:08:59,979
Let's not talk about how my generation's aerospace engineers started everything from zero.

119
00:08:59,979 --> 00:09:02,639
Look at your colleague, Guan Zai.

120
00:09:02,639 --> 00:09:05,519
He gave up his high-paying job and came back from the US.

121
00:09:05,519 --> 00:09:08,038
I always thought you were like him,

122
00:09:08,038 --> 00:09:11,879
that you had your own belief and persistence.

123
00:09:20,199 --> 00:09:23,018
Yu Tu gave up his high-paying job too.

124
00:09:27,199 --> 00:09:31,738
Yu Tu and his colleague are talented people. They deserve the best treatment.

125
00:09:31,738 --> 00:09:37,478
But asking them to have no regard for anything else for the sake of their dream, isn't this...

126
00:09:41,839 --> 00:09:43,998
isn't it like kidnapping? 
  (T/N: a guilt trip) 

127
00:09:44,759 --> 00:09:46,359
Jingjing!

128
00:10:03,079 --> 00:10:04,579
Sorry.

129
00:10:16,996 --> 00:10:20,096
Professor, I apologize.

130
00:10:20,099 --> 00:10:22,738
We won't disturb you and your wife's dinner.

131
00:10:47,698 --> 00:10:50,759
You're the biggest beneficiary of our current society,

132
00:10:50,759 --> 00:10:53,179
so you shouldn't say those things to my professor.

133
00:10:57,499 --> 00:10:59,319
What do you mean?

134
00:10:59,998 --> 00:11:04,558
If I'm not Qiao Jingjing, if I'm not a celebrity, would I be able to say it?

135
00:11:04,558 --> 00:11:07,098
I just wanted to defend you.

136
00:11:10,598 --> 00:11:14,419
I want you to be an aerospace engineer more than anyone else.

137
00:11:28,118 --> 00:11:29,818
Why?

138
00:11:34,399 --> 00:11:38,738
Jingjing. Teacher Yu. Why are you guys out here?

139
00:12:52,478 --> 00:12:55,979
Can you delete the photo you took just now?

140
00:13:02,839 --> 00:13:04,139
Thank you.

141
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:32,459
 I'm sorry. 

142
00:13:53,558 --> 00:13:55,758
 Don't take what your professor said to heart. 

143
00:13:55,758 --> 00:13:59,118
 He was just a bit upset. We respect your decision. 

144
00:13:59,118 --> 00:14:03,399
 Also, don't blame your friend. What she said was true. 

145
00:14:10,358 --> 00:14:12,358
 Thank you, Professor Wang. 

