00:15:56,920 --> 00:16:01,000
 Yu Tu, Satellite JX has some emergency issues. The attitude is out of control. 

160
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,240
 I don't care where you are. 

161
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:08,140
 Your break is terminated, get to Northwest Satellite Control Center immediately. 

162
00:16:19,558 --> 00:16:21,258
Open the trunk, please.

163
00:16:28,319 --> 00:16:29,519
What happened?

164
00:16:29,519 --> 00:16:32,499
Did Old Hu summon you with one phone call?

165
00:16:32,499 --> 00:16:36,818
I grabbed some documents from the institute and took the last flight to Xi'an.

166
00:16:36,818 --> 00:16:37,959
Why are you out here?

167
00:16:37,959 --> 00:16:40,578
I flew over from Beijing. I arrived just a little earlier than you.

168
00:16:40,578 --> 00:16:43,060
Old Hu said you'd be here, so I was waiting for you.

169
00:16:43,060 --> 00:16:46,218
What happened exactly? They didn't tell me anything.

170
00:16:46,218 --> 00:16:48,218
Let's go in first.

171
00:16:54,519 --> 00:16:58,498
Are you two the staff from Unit 158? IDs, please.

172
00:17:02,118 --> 00:17:04,138
These are your passes. Follow me.

173
00:17:04,138 --> 00:17:05,338
Okay.

174
00:17:06,299 --> 00:17:07,699
Here.

175
00:17:17,478 --> 00:17:20,940
JX was working properly.

176
00:17:20,940 --> 00:17:23,200
But last night, after it finished its first rotation,

177
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:26,030
the ground station did not receive any telemetry signal.

178
00:17:26,038 --> 00:17:30,238
The center informed us straight away.

179
00:17:30,238 --> 00:17:32,130
They fixed channels transmission from the ground station,

180
00:17:32,130 --> 00:17:34,950
RF module from the transponder, issuing commands to the back-up,

181
00:17:34,950 --> 00:17:36,790
they did it thrice

182
00:17:36,790 --> 00:17:41,090
but they still couldn't receive the telemetry signal from the satellite.

183
00:17:41,098 --> 00:17:43,018
Did it just go MIA (Missing In Action)?

184
00:17:43,958 --> 00:17:46,478
No response even from the backup?

185
00:17:46,478 --> 00:17:47,978
Yes.

186
00:17:47,978 --> 00:17:52,018
The backup transponder on Satellite JX is heterogeneous.

187
00:17:52,018 --> 00:17:54,738
The possibility of a simultaneous error is extremely low.

188
00:17:54,738 --> 00:17:58,378
But it happened. We are the first to arrive from our team.

189
00:17:58,378 --> 00:18:00,700
Others who worked on JX

190
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:03,530
are occupied. They'll be here by tomorrow.

191
