246
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:18,625
Old Guan. Old Guan.

247
00:22:18,625 --> 00:22:20,640
Did we find the satellite?

248
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:25,040
No, but I might have found an explanation.

249
00:22:30,460 --> 00:22:32,720
All right. Let's have a meeting.

250
00:22:40,379 --> 00:22:43,399
    
 Solar energetic particle is already a rare phenomenon.

251
00:22:43,399 --> 00:22:47,616
But to have one whose energy affects two machines at the same time?

252
00:22:47,616 --> 00:22:50,320
This is too unlikely.

253
00:22:50,320 --> 00:22:54,676
Previously, we've been focusing on the satellite itself,

254
00:22:54,676 --> 00:22:56,480
and we couldn't locate the problem.

255
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:58,580
I was exploring the possibility of external factors

256
00:22:58,580 --> 00:23:02,620
and I suddenly thought of the solar wind forecast I saw earlier.

257
00:23:02,620 --> 00:23:05,930
I consulted the International Space Web,

258
00:23:05,930 --> 00:23:08,370
and I did find some relevant info.

259
00:23:08,375 --> 00:23:10,060
While we were waiting for you all,

260
00:23:10,060 --> 00:23:13,559
Chief Guan and I did a rough calculation.

261
00:23:13,559 --> 00:23:15,760
This possibility cannot be ruled out

262
