325
00:27:26,460 --> 00:27:29,319
Please check every system now.

326
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:35,120
How's the satellite?

327
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:37,960
 Stabilization subsystem malfunction. Three-axis earth-oriented stabilization failed. 

328
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:42,600
The power system is normal. But there's excessive power supply. It used less power than expected.

329
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:46,439
We did take into account the damage to the stabilization subsystem due to the solar storm.

330
00:27:46,439 --> 00:27:49,620
We have a plan for this exact scenario.

331
00:27:49,620 --> 00:27:51,159
The power supply malfunction

332
00:27:51,159 --> 00:27:53,960
must be the side product of the damaged stabilization subsystem.

333
00:27:53,960 --> 00:27:57,000
 I think it is because of the solar sails, that we can't establish solar orientation properly, 

334
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:59,459
 so the power supply has increased. 

335
00:27:59,459 --> 00:28:02,919
Our utmost priority now is to reduce the workload on the satellite.

336
00:28:02,919 --> 00:28:07,119
Contain its energy consumption and correct its attitude as soon as possible.

337
00:28:07,119 --> 00:28:09,260
Follow the protocol and launch the commands.

338
00:28:09,260 --> 00:28:12,780
Turn off all unnecessary devices and lessen power consumption.

339
00:28:12,780 --> 00:28:18,243
